# Git & GitHub Workflow

No Jira — track work in **GitHub Issues** and the repo **Project board**. OpenSpec remains the spec source of truth; issues provide cross-links and audit history.

## Branches

- **`master`** — default; always deployable. No direct commits for feature work.
- **Feature branches** — one branch per OpenSpec change or fix:
  - `feat/<change-name>` — new capability (`/apply`)
  - `fix/<topic>` — bug fixes
  - `chore/<topic>` — CI, docs, tooling
- Create the branch at `/apply` (or before, for chores). Push early; open a **draft PR** linked to the issue.

## Issues

- Create or reference a GitHub Issue **before** `/apply` when the work is non-trivial.
- Title format: `[<change-name>] Short description` (e.g. `[cleanup-insights] Open folder in explorer`).
- Issue body MUST include:
  - Link to `openspec/changes/<change-name>/` (or note that `/enrich-us` is needed)
  - Acceptance criteria (copy from `user-story.md` or task list)
  - Target branch name
- Labels: `change`, `area:*`, `priority:*` as applicable.
- Close the issue in the PR description (`Closes #N`) when merging after `/archive`.

## Project board

- Repo project: **disk-tool** (GitHub Projects v2).
- Status columns map to SPECBOOT stages:

| Column | SPECBOOT stage |
|--------|----------------|
| Backlog | `/enrich-us` or `/propose` not started |
| Ready | proposal artifacts complete, issue open |
| In progress | branch + `/apply` |
| In review | PR open, `/verify` + `/code-review` |
| Done | merged to `master`, `/archive` complete |

- Move the linked issue when changing stage; keep OpenSpec `tasks.md` in sync.

## Pull requests

- Target: `master`.
- Title: same as issue or `[change-name] summary`.
- Body: `Closes #N`, summary, test plan, link to `testing-report.md`.
- CI must be green before merge.
- Merge via squash or merge commit per team preference; delete branch after merge.

## Traceability chain

```
GitHub Issue → feature branch → PR → CI → merge → closes issue → OpenSpec archive
```

Every merged change should be recoverable from issue + PR + `openspec/changes/<name>/` history.
